Lagos state Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu has said lauded the Lagos State Marathon as a symbol of the spirit of Lagos. He noted that 41 km marathon has become a yearly ritual for athletes. The Governor said the marathon embodied the spirit of Lagos, which teaches endurance, perseverance and resilience while toiling through physical strength.   Ethiopians win 2022 Lagos City Marathon     Osimhen shines as Napoli hold Inter     KIFA signs MOU with Ilaji Hotels and Sports Resort   He said: “One of the objectives of this event is to put Lagos on a global platform in the area of sport. Every year, new records are broken and the marathon gets bigger and better. As a Government, we are fully committed to sustaining this noble initiative and leading from the front to ensure that all participants, especially, our youths, get the best from this event. “I acknowledge the great work which Access Bank and all other sponsors have put in to make this edition a success. The goal of the marathon is to use sport as a tool to promote physical fitness, togetherness, resilience and every virtue that can make human beings progress and live fulfilling life. This is the strongest rallying point for our youths and next edition would be better than what we have had this year.” - Advertisement - Sanwo-Olu completed 8km in 40m, taking off from the State House in Marina, to finish at Eko Atlantic City. The Governor was accompanied by his deputy, Dr. Obafemi Hamzat, Minister for Sport and Youth Development, Mr. Sunday Dare, Deputy Governor of Edo State, Comrade Philip Shuaibu, Lagos Head of Service, Mr. Hakeem Muri-Okunola, Chairman of Lagos State Sports Commission (LSSC), Shola Aiyepeku, and LSSC Director-General, Gafaar Bolowotan, among other top functionaries, to participate in the symbolic flag-off. SPONSORED